<para id="fs-id1164567577800">Therefore, we expect a newborn to wake its mother after midnight 2.1 times per week, on the average.</para><para id="fs-id1164567878100">To calculate the standard deviation <emphasis effect="italics">σ</emphasis>, we add the fourth column (<emphasis effect="italics">x-μ</emphasis>)<sup>2</sup> and the fifth column <m:math><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mi>μ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>∙</m:mo><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:math> to get the following table:</para><table id="fs-id1164567849065" summary="A five column, six row table is shown. The header row contains the following column titles: x, P opening parenthesis x closing parenthesis, x P opening parenthesis x closing parenthesis, opening parenthesis x minus mu closing parenthesis superscript two, and opening parenthesis x minus mu closing parenthesis superscript 2 multiplication dot P opening parenthesis x closing parenthesis. The first data row contains 0; P opening parenthesis x equals 0 closing parenthesis equals two fiftieths; opening parenthesis 0 closing parenthesis opening parenthesis two fiftieths closing parenthesis equals 0; opening parenthesis 0 minus 2.1 closing parenthesis superscript two equals 4.41; and 4.41 multiplication dot two fiftieths = 0.1764. The second data row contains 1; P opening parenthesis x equals 1 closing parenthesis equals eleven fiftieths; opening parenthesis 1 closing parenthesis opening parenthesis eleven fiftieths closing parenthesis equals eleven fiftieths; opening parenthesis 1 minus 2.1 closing parenthesis superscript two equals 1.21; and 1.21 multiplication dot eleven fiftieths = 0.2662. The third data row contains 2; P opening parenthesis x equals 2 closing parenthesis equals twenty-three fiftieths; opening parenthesis 2 closing parenthesis opening parenthesis twenty-three fiftieths clo