  <para id="eip-id1164900324701">The variable of interest is <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis>, or the gain or loss, in dollars.</para><para id="eip-id1164893101611">The face cards jack, queen, and king. There are (3)(4) = 12 face cards and 52 – 12 = 40 cards that are not face cards.</para><para id="eip-id1164889621862">We first need to construct the probability distribution for <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis>. We use the card and coin events to determine the probability for each outcome, but we use the monetary value of <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis> to determine the expected value.</para>

